#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:4
msgid "functions - print or erase functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:9
msgid ""
"functions [-a | --all] [-n | --names]\n"
"functions [-D | --details] [-v] FUNCTION\n"
"functions -c OLDNAME NEWNAME\n"
"functions -d DESCRIPTION FUNCTION\n"
"functions [-e | -q] FUNCTION ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:18
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:20
msgid "``functions`` prints or erases functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:22
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:24
msgid "**-a** or **--all**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:25
msgid "Lists all functions, even those whose name starts with an underscore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:27
msgid "**-c** or **--copy** *OLDNAME* *NEWNAME*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:28
msgid ""
"Creates a new function named *NEWNAME*, using the definition of the "
"*OLDNAME* function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:30
msgid "**-d** or **--description** *DESCRIPTION*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:31
msgid "Changes the description of this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:33
msgid "**-e** or **--erase**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:34
msgid ""
"Causes the specified functions to be erased. This also means that it is "
"prevented from autoloading in the current session. Use :doc:`funcsave "
"<funcsave>` to remove the saved copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:36
msgid "**-D** or **--details**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:37
msgid ""
"Reports the path name where the specified function is defined or could be "
"autoloaded, ``stdin`` if the function was defined interactively or on the "
"command line or by reading standard input, **-** if the function was created "
"via :doc:`source <source>`, and ``n/a`` if the function isn't available. "
"(Functions created via :doc:`alias <alias>` will return **-**, because "
"``alias`` uses ``source`` internally.) If the **--verbose** option is also "
"specified then five lines are written:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:39
msgid "the pathname as already described,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:40
msgid "``autoloaded``, ``not-autoloaded`` or ``n/a``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:41
msgid "the line number within the file or zero if not applicable,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:42
msgid ""
"``scope-shadowing`` if the function shadows the vars in the calling function "
"(the normal case if it wasn't defined with **--no-scope-shadowing**), else "
"``no-scope-shadowing``, or ``n/a`` if the function isn't defined,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:43
msgid ""
"the function description minimally escaped so it is a single line, or ``n/"
"a`` if the function isn't defined or has no description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:45
msgid ""
"You should not assume that only five lines will be written since we may add "
"additional information to the output in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:47
msgid "**--no-details**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:48
msgid ""
"Turns off function path reporting, so just the definition will be printed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:50
msgid "**-n** or **--names**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:51
msgid "Lists the names of all defined functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:53
msgid "**-q** or **--query**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:54
msgid "Tests if the specified functions exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:56
msgid "**-v** or **--verbose**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:57
msgid "Make some output more verbose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:59
msgid "**-H** or **--handlers**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:60
msgid "Show all event handlers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:62
msgid "**-t** or **--handlers-type** *TYPE*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:63
msgid "Show all event handlers matching the given *TYPE*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:65
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:66
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:68
msgid ""
"The default behavior of ``functions``, when called with no arguments, is to "
"print the names of all defined functions. Unless the ``-a`` option is given, "
"no functions starting with underscores are included in the output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:70
msgid ""
"If any non-option parameters are given, the definition of the specified "
"functions are printed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:72
msgid ""
"Copying a function using ``-c`` copies only the body of the function, and "
"does not attach any event notifications from the original function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:74
msgid ""
"Only one function's description can be changed in a single invocation of "
"``functions -d``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:76
msgid ""
"The exit status of ``functions`` is the number of functions specified in the "
"argument list that do not exist, which can be used in concert with the ``-"
"q`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:80
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:85
msgid ""
"functions -n\n"
"# Displays a list of currently-defined functions\n"
"\n"
"functions -c foo bar\n"
"# Copies the 'foo' function to a new function called 'bar'\n"
"\n"
"functions -e bar\n"
"# Erases the function ``bar``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:95
msgid "See more"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/functions.rst:97
msgid ""
"For more explanation of how functions fit into fish, see :ref:`Functions "
"<syntax-function>`."
msgstr ""
